# chord minimal example: no selects, no root/degree -> C Lydian, smart default =
# all seven scale notes. The four voices take the FIRST FOUR notes in INTERVAL
# (select-input) order: select1/3/5/7 = root/3rd/5th/7th = C,E,G,B -> a C major 7.
# pitch=0, spread=0, inversion=0 -> voiced within one octave, lowest note nearest
# above pitch (C at 0 V). 1 semitone = 0.1/12 = 0.0083333 engine.
#   O1=C(semi 0), O2=E(4), O3=G(7), O4=B(11)
patch <<<
[chord]
    output1 = O1
    output2 = O2
    output3 = O3
    output4 = O4
>>>
@0 expect O1 0 tol 1e-5
@0 expect O2 0.0333333 tol 1e-5
@0 expect O3 0.0583333 tol 1e-5
@0 expect O4 0.0916667 tol 1e-5
